BENIN – The Obaseki/Shaibu Movement (OSM), on Tuesday, commended President Muhammadu Buhari for appointing Chief Bisi Akande to head the APC National Reconciliation Committee. The political pressure group, which made the commendation in a communiqué it issued at the end of its meeting in Benin City, described Akande as a seasoned politician and elder statesman whose sense of judgement would not be faulted. According to the communiqué, which was read by Damian Lawani, the state Commissioner for Youth and Sports, “we are giving Kudos to Mr. President, Muhammadu Buhari, for appointing Chief Bisi Akande, a man of impeccable character, to head the long awaited APC National Reconciliation Committee. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network “We also want to use this opportunity to commend the good governance of Governor Godwin Obaseki and his deputy, Rt Hon. Philip Shaibu, for repositioning Edo State in the areas of infrastructural development, education, job creation, security, health care, human capacity building and many more.